  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read CacheModule.cs (post-task-003 state). Identify the 4 branches and their externally observable effects.</step>
    <step order="2">Read NullConnectionMultiplexer.cs (post-task-004 state). Identify observable surface: Subscribe is no-op, Publish returns 0, GetDatabase throws.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `CacheModuleTests.cs`. Use existing test conventions in `Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` (xUnit, FluentAssertions probably).</step>
    <step order="4">Test 1 — Redis_On_RegistersConnectionMultiplexer: mock ConnectionMultiplexer via test fixture; verify `IConnectionMultiplexer` resolves to a non-null instance; verify `IDistributedCache` resolves to RedisCache (not memory cache).</step>
    <step order="5">Test 2 — Redis_Off_AllowFallback_Dev_RegistersInMemoryAndNullMultiplexer: set `IHostEnvironment` mock to Development; verify `IDistributedCache` resolves to `MemoryDistributedCache`; verify `IConnectionMultiplexer` resolves to `NullConnectionMultiplexer`.</step>
    <step order="6">Test 3 — Redis_Off_AllowFallback_NonDev_Throws: set `IHostEnvironment` to "Staging"; assert `InvalidOperationException` thrown during `BuildServiceProvider()`; verify message contains "Development environments" + actual env name.</step>
    <step order="7">Test 4 — Redis_Off_NoFallbackOptIn_Throws: assert `InvalidOperationException`; verify message contains "Set Redis:Enabled=true".</step>
    <step order="8">Test 5 — NullConnectionMultiplexer_Subscribe_IsNoOp: instantiate directly; verify `GetSubscriber().Subscribe(...)` does not throw; verify callback is never invoked (use a sentinel bool).</step>
    <step order="9">Test 6 — NullConnectionMultiplexer_GetDatabase_Throws: verify `GetDatabase().StringGetAsync("foo")` throws `NotSupportedException` with the prescribed message.</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Infrastructure/DI/CacheModuleTests.cs --filter "FullyQualifiedName~CacheModuleTests"`. All 6 pass.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `TASK-INDEX.md` + `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>
